  "prompt": "Why was the wax museum in Philadelphia built?",
  "response": "The Wax Museum in Philadelphia, also known as the Philadelphia Wax Museum, was built to provide an engaging and educational experience for visitors by showcasing life-like wax figures of historical figures, celebrities, and other notable personalities. Established in 1979, it aimed to attract tourists and locals alike, offering them a chance to learn about history and culture in an interactive way. The museum was located in the historic district of Philadelphia, which added to its appeal as a destination for those interested in American history.",
